!!!
%html
  %head
    %title SassBass test page
    %link{:href => '/sassbass.css', :rel => :stylesheet, :type => 'text/css'}
  %body
    #contents
      %h1 SassBass is a collection of useful sass files.
      %p 
        These are a collection of files I have gathered from around the web as well as popular CSS libraries converted into SASS format.

      .file-information
        %h2 reset.sass
        %p This is a SASS version of the yahoo reset file.
        %pre.code-sample
          @import reset

      .file-information
        %h2 css3please.sass
        %p Mixins for the classes hosted on <a href='http://css3please.com'>css3please.com</a>
        %pre.code-sample
          :preserve
            @import css3please
            .simple-message
              +box-round(5px)
              +box-gradient(#fff, #ddd)
              +box-shadow(0, 0, 3px, #888)
              border: 1px solid #aaa
              padding: 10px

        .simple-message
          hello, i am a simple message


      .file-information
        %h2 simple_mixins.sass
        %p DRY versions of commonly used CSS properties and patterns to help build pleasing pages faster.


        %h3 Global mixins
        %pre.code-sample
          :preserve
            @import simple_mixins
            .mixin-dark
              +global-style-dark

        .mixin-dark
          %p this is a test of the global dark mixin

        %pre.code-sample
          :preserve
            @import simple_mixins
            .mixin-light
              +global-style-light

        .mixin-light
          %p this is a test of the global light mixin
           
        %pre.code-sample
          :preserve
            @import simple_mixins 
            .mixin-sandbox
              +paint(#97D467)
              +relative
              color: darken(#97D467, 20%)
              padding-right: 50px
              padding: 10px
             
            .mixin-dialog
              +absolute
              +drop-shadow
              +monospace
              +paint(#ddd)
              color: #888
              padding: 2px
              right: 10px
              top: 10px

        .mixin-sandbox
          %p 
            this is a more complidated test. it uses multiple mixins
            to create a pretty green box with a small message inside.
          %p 
            the message is absolutely positioned and has a drop 
            shadow.


          .mixin-dialog
            hello

      .file-information
        %h2 css3_buttons.sass
        %p Mixins for the buttons created by <a href='https://github.com/ubuwaits/css3-buttons'>ubuwaits</a>
        
        :ruby
          buttons = %w{ios-blue ios-purple ios-yellow minimal clean-gray clean-green pale-blue blue-pill dribble slick-black thoughtbot}
        - buttons.each do |b|
          %div
            %pre.code-sample
              :preserve
                .button.#{b}
                  +button-#{b}
            %span.button{:class => b}= b.gsub('-', ' ')

